{{Infobox journal | title = Archiv für das Studium der neueren Sprachen und Literaturen | cover = | editor = Christa Jansohn | discipline = [[Linguistics]], [[literature]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English, German, Romance languages | former_names = | abbreviation = Arch. Stud. Neuer. Sprachen Lit. | publisher = [[Erich Schmidt Verlag]] | country = Germany | frequency = Biannually | history = 1846–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.archivdigital.info/homepage.html | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 457008267 | LCCN = 10032834 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0003-8970 | eISSN = | boxwidth = }}
'''''Archiv für das Studium der neueren Sprachen und Literaturen''''' is the oldest{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}} modern [[philological]] journal, founded in 1846 by [[Ludwig Herrig]] and [[Heinrich Viehoff]]. The first two volumes were published by Julius Bädeker Verlag Elberfeld and Iserlohn and for the next 120 years by [[Georg Westermann Verlag Braunschweig]] (now Westermann Druck- und Verlagsgruppe). Since 1979, the journal is published by [[Erich Schmidt Verlag]], Berlin. The articles, smaller contributions and reviews are written in German, English, and Romance languages. The current [[editor-in-chief]] is Christa Jansohn ([[University of Bamberg]]).
