'''Tel Tzora''', ({{lang-he|תל צרעה}}), is a [[Tell (archaeology)|tell]] and [[Israel]]i [[Archaeology|archaeological]] site west of [[Jerusalem]] near the modern-day [[kibbutz]] [[Tzora|of the same name]], and more commonly identified with the depopulated Palestinian village of [[Sar'a]]. Nearby is the well-known tourist attraction regarded by many as the location of [[Samson]]'s tomb.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=uj7Dqe2rngEC&pg=PT228&lpg=PT228&dq=tel+tzora&source=bl&ots=ZWEGM0VALq&sig=sQh9YwwwMddvZVyFvVT0ekukFKY&hl=en&ei=tpuqSt_5M4qQ6APQ_Zj8Bw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10#v=onepage&q=tel%20tzora&f=false IsraGuide 2007/2008 (pb) - I. M. Levinger, Kalman Neuman - Google Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

